<title>USA: Bay to buy ISOTRO for $11 million cash.</title>
<headline>Bay to buy ISOTRO for $11 million cash.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA CLARA, Calif. 1997-04-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bay Networks Inc said Wednesday it had agreed to acquire ISOTRO Network Management Inc of Canada for $11 million cash.</p>
<p>Bay said it expects to recognize a substantial portion of the acquisition price as a one-time charge for in-process technology. It said this is consistent with standard accounting practice for technology-related acquisitions.</p>
<p>On the closing of the transaction, ISOTRO Chief Executive Officer Rod Anderson will report to Brad Noblet, vice president and general manager of Bay's Router product division.</p>
